Unrelated but makes me think: wouldn't a `vim.set` module be useful for the stdlib? It would just create tables likes these from arrays and include useful functions like disjoint, intersection, sub/supersets, union, etc.

```lua
local s = vim.set.new({ 'a', 'b', 'a' }) -- { a = true, b = true }
vim.set.union(s, vim.set.new({ 'b' }) -- { a = true }
vim.set.values(s) -- (or `asarray()`) { 'a', 'b' }
```
